headline: Boeing Stock Rises After NTSB Crash Report. Analysts Remain Bullish.
summary: Boeing  stock is having another good day.  Shares of the commercial jet maker were up 1.9% at $247.28 in midday trading, while the  and  were up 0.6% and 0.8%, respectively.  The move came after an accident update from the National Transportation Safety Board regarding the United Parcel Service MD-11 cargo jet that crashed shortly after takeoff in Kentucky on Nov. 4, 2025, killing 14 and injuring 23 more.
